<DOC><DOCNO> AP880406-0024 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-06-88 0300EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Italy-Strikes     04-06 0145</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Italy-Strikes,0149</SECOND><HEAD>More Airport Strikes Announced In Italy</HEAD><DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ground personnel at Rome's Leonardo Da Vinci airportannounced they will stage 12-hour strikes on April 16 and 24.   The Italian news agency ANSA said the strikes are expected toforce the cancellation or postponement of most flights on those twodays.   Union leaders on Tuesday said the strike would not interferewith flights for emergency, military or government purposes.Flights to and from Italy's islands also will not be interrupted.   Waves of recent airline and railway strikes in Italy over thelast five months have made traveling difficult to plan.   Ground crews have been negotiating for a new contract for eightmonths. For the last five months, the crews have staged periodicstrikes.   They are demanding better working conditions in the controltowers, salary increases and fewer hours in the work week.</TEXT></DOC>